free_txt: EXPERIMENTAL SITE.
J.F., P.K., E.R., C.S., H.S., K.S.
J.E., Z.F., J.K., Z.K., Z.S.
CYCLOTRON AT THE PAUL SCHERRER
INSTITUTE, SWITZERLAND. HIGH ENERGY NEUTRON BEAM.
S.W.
.CORRECTIONS WERE APPLIED FOR TIME DRIFTS AND FOR THE
OVERLAP OF SPECTRA FROM NEIGHBOURING BUNCHES, THIS
LATTER CORRECTION BEING BASED ON QUASI-TWO-BODY
SCALING. CORRECTIONS WERE ALSO APPLIED FOR AIR BACK-
GROUND (FROM SAMPLE-OUT MEAUSUREMENTS), DEAD-TIME, AND
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY. THE AIR BACKGROUND CORRECTION WAS
ALWAYS LESS THAN 6% WITH A MAXIMUM CONTRIBUTION AT
164 DEG.
EACH TELESCOPE CONSISTED OF TWO
THIN (1.5 OR 2 MM) PLASTIC SCINTILLATORS AND A THIRD
ONE 30 CM IN LENGTH, THE TOF MEASUREMENT BEING MADE
ON THE DISTANCE OF 1.3 - 2.1 M BETWEEN THE TWO THIN
DETECTORS. ENERGY SPECTRA WERE MEASURED AT FIVE ANGLES
FROM 54 TO 164 DEGREES.
.AN ADDITIONAL COUNTER ARRAY SERVED AS A BEAM MONITOR.
IT WAS DIRECTED TOWARDS ANOTHER SCINTILLATOR PLACED IN
THE NEUTRON BEAM APPROX 0.5 M IN FRONT OF THE REACTION
TARGET WHICH WAS USED AS A VETO COUNTER.
STATISTICAL ERRORS. IN ADDITION THERE IS A 7%
UNCERTAINTY IN THE NEUTRON FLUX DETERMINATION AND A
UNCERTAINTY OF UP TO 5% IN THE SUBTRACTION OF THE
BACKGROUND DUE TO LOW ENERGY NEUTRONS FROM PRECEDING
BUNCHES DETERMINED USING THE QUASI-TWO-BODY SCALING
MODEL.
CYCLOTRON AT THE PAUL SCHERRER
INSTITUTE, SWITZERLAND. HIGH ENERGY NEUTRON BEAM.
.P-C12, 11 CM THICK CARBON TARGET, BOMBARDED WITH
590 MEV PROTONS. NEUTRONS EMITTED AT AN ANGLE OF
60 MRAD LEAVE TARGET STATION THROUGH A HOLE IN THE
BEAM DUMP AND ARE COLLIMATED TO A BEAM SIZE OF ABOUT
1 X 1 CM2 AT THE POSITION OF THE REACTION TARGET
PLACED AT A DISTANCE OF 21.2 M. THE NEUTRONS WERE
PRODUCED IN 0.8 NS WIDE (FWHM) BUNCHES WITH A
REPETITION TIME OF 19.75 NS.
.CONTINOUS NEUTRON SPECTRA WITH A DOMINANT 40 MEV WIDE
PEAK AT 545 MEV NEUTRON ENERGY.
USED IN DETERMINATION OF NEUTRON ENERGY. SIX
NEUTRON ENERGY BINS WERE CONSIDERED IN THE EXPERIMENT,
EACH CORRESPONDING TO A WIDTH OF 3 NS ON THE TIME-OF-
FLIGHT SCALE.
ALSO USED IN THE DETERMINTATION OF THE CP
ENERGY IN THE DETECTOR TELESCOPES.
NP SCATTERING AT 54 DEG FROM A
POLYETHYLENE TARGET USED TO DETERMINE THE SHAPE AND
ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE NEUTRON SPECTRUM.
